{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix signed/unsigned integer comparison mismatch in S1AP assoc_id handling\n\n### Summary\nThe S1AP module was using incorrect printf format specifiers for the `assoc_id` parameter, which is defined as a signed 32-bit integer (`sctp_assoc_t` maps to `__s32`) but was being formatted with `%u` (unsigned int) in multiple logging statements. This could lead to incorrect interpretation of negative association IDs, particularly the special value `-1` used to indicate \"no association\".\n\nThe issue was introduced when the codebase was originally written and propagated through multiple files in the S1AP implementation. This mismatch could cause incorrect logging output and potentially affect downstream logic that relies on correct string representations of association IDs.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/S1AP/s1ap_eNB_handlers.c`: Updated all instances of `%u` to `%d` for `assoc_id` parameters in logging statements\n- `openair3/S1AP/s1ap_eNB_nas_procedures.c`: Fixed format specifiers for `assoc_id` in error and debug messages  \n- `openair3/S1AP/s1ap_eNB_overload.c`: Corrected format specifiers in error handling paths\n\n"
}